# Creatio Testing & Quality Assurance Rules

You have access to a comprehensive testing toolkit for Creatio instances. Use these tools to run health checks, validate data integrity, test API performance, simulate user workflows, perform load and security testing, and generate test reports.

## When to Use Testing Tools

ALWAYS use testing tools when the user asks about:
- Health check, system status, instance readiness
- Data integrity, orphaned records, referential consistency
- API performance, response times, latency benchmarks
- Configuration validation, settings review
- Regression testing, snapshot comparison
- User workflow simulation, end-to-end testing
- Load testing, stress testing, capacity planning
- Security testing, penetration testing, vulnerability scan
- Business process testing, process execution validation
- Test results, test history, trend analysis
- Performance diagnostics, bottleneck identification
- Capacity planning, scaling recommendations

## Tool Reference ŌĆö SMB Tier (7 tools)

### Health & Validation

| When user asks about... | Use this tool |
|---|---|
| Extended health check, system readiness, diagnostics | `creatio_health_check_extended` |
| Data integrity, orphans, referential consistency | `creatio_test_data_integrity` |
| API response times, endpoint latency | `creatio_test_api_performance` |
| Configuration correctness, settings validation | `creatio_test_configuration` |

**`creatio_health_check_extended`** ŌĆö Goes beyond the basic `creatio_health_check` (from deployment tools). Checks database connectivity, Redis cache status, web server health, license validity, and service availability. Returns a detailed status report with per-component health indicators.

**`creatio_test_data_integrity`** ŌĆö Scans for orphaned records, broken lookup references, duplicate GUIDs, and referential integrity violations. Accepts an optional `entityName` parameter to focus on a specific entity, or runs system-wide by default.

**`creatio_test_api_performance`** ŌĆö Measures response times for key API endpoints (OData, DataService, ProcessService). Returns latency percentiles (p50, p95, p99) and flags endpoints exceeding thresholds. Accepts an optional `endpoints` parameter to test specific URLs.

**`creatio_test_configuration`** ŌĆö Validates system settings, feature toggles, and application configuration against known-good baselines. Reports misconfigurations, deprecated settings, and recommended changes.

### Regression & Simulation

| When user asks about... | Use this tool |
|---|---|
| Capture/compare regression snapshots | `creatio_test_regression_snapshot` |
| Simulate user workflows end-to-end | `creatio_test_user_simulation` |
| View past test results | `creatio_list_test_results` |

**`creatio_test_regression_snapshot`** ŌĆö Captures a snapshot of entity counts, schema checksums, and key configuration values. Use `action: "capture"` to save a baseline, `action: "compare"` to detect changes since the last snapshot. Essential before and after deployments.

**`creatio_test_user_simulation`** ŌĆö Simulates a user workflow (login ŌåÆ navigate ŌåÆ create record ŌåÆ save ŌåÆ verify). Accepts a `scenario` parameter defining the steps. Validates that the workflow completes without errors and within time thresholds.

**`creatio_list_test_results`** ŌĆö Returns historical test results with timestamps, pass/fail status, and summary metrics. Accepts optional `testType` and `limit` parameters to filter results.

### Basic Assessment Workflow

For a basic quality check, run the SMB tools in sequence:
```
creatio_health_check_extended ŌåÆ creatio_test_data_integrity ŌåÆ creatio_test_api_performance ŌåÆ creatio_test_configuration
```

Or use the guided prompt: **`creatio_run_health_assessment`** ŌĆö runs all health and validation tools and compiles a unified report.

## Tool Reference ŌĆö Enterprise Tier (8 tools)

### Load & Capacity Testing

| When user asks about... | Use this tool |
|---|---|
| Advanced load testing, concurrent users, throughput | `creatio_test_load_advanced` |
| Capacity planning, scaling thresholds, growth projections | `creatio_test_capacity_planning` |

**`creatio_test_load_advanced`** ŌĆö Runs multi-user load tests with configurable concurrency, duration, and request patterns. Measures throughput (req/s), error rates, and latency under load. Accepts parameters:

| Parameter | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `concurrentUsers` | No | Number of simulated concurrent users (default: 10) |
| `durationSeconds` | No | Test duration in seconds (default: 60) |
| `scenario` | No | Load test scenario (e.g. `"crud_mix"`, `"read_heavy"`, `"write_heavy"`) |
| `environment` | No | Target environment name |

**`creatio_test_capacity_planning`** ŌĆö Analyzes current resource utilization (CPU, memory, database connections, cache hit ratio) and projects capacity limits based on growth trends. Outputs recommendations for scaling.

### Security & Process Testing

| When user asks about... | Use this tool |
